{
  "texts": [
    "Preprocessing was carried out using weighting or MetaCost.",
    "For instance, Wang et al. (2013) implemented cost-sensitive logistic regression and decision trees by weighting training instances based on the total cost associated with each class in the provided cost matrix.",
    "In another study, Afzal et al. (2013) employed MetaCost to integrate cost sensitivity into four ML models.",
    "Preprocessing techniques are adopted by researchers as they alter the training data instead of the underlying algorithm (Fernández et al. 2018), rendering them a suitable approach for different types of classifiers.",
    "On the other hand, postprocessing relied on thresholding."
  ]
}